Canada is issuing an 80 billion yeneurobond due June 25, 1992 paying 4-3/8 pct and priced at101-1/2 pct, lead manager Nomura International Ltd said.    The non-callable bond is available in denominations of onemln and 10 mln yen and will be listed in Luxembourg. Theselling concession is 1-1/4 pct while management andunderwriting combined pays 5/8 pct.    Payment date is June 25. REUTER&#3;